Consent: INFORMATION AND CONSENT FORM    Study Title: Multi-cultural investigation of the Mental Accounting effect  Researcher: Caroline Roux  Researcher’s Contact Information: caroline.roux@concordia.ca  Project Leader: Enrico Rubaltelli  Project Leader’s Contact Information: jdmlab.multicountry@gmail.com  Source of funding for the study: N/A    You are being invited to participate in the research study mentioned above. This form provides information about what participating would mean. Please read it carefully before deciding if you want to participate or not. If there is anything you do not understand, or if you want more information, please ask the researcher.    A. PURPOSE  - The purpose of this research is to replicate previous studies that investigated the mental accounting effect.    B. PROCEDURES  - If you participate, you will be asked to answer questions about various scenarios, financial literacy, and demographic information.  - You understand that you will not need to provide any identifying information in this study.  - In total, participating in this study will take 15 minutes.    C. RISKS AND BENEFITS  - You understand that there are no known risks associated with participating in this study. Participants who have completed similar studies in the past did not report any adverse effects.  - You will not receive any compensation for participating in this study. This research is not intended to benefit you personally.    D. CONFIDENTIALITY  - We will gather the following information as part of this research: your answers to the study’s questions. We will not allow anyone to access the information, except people directly involved in conducting the research. We will only use the information for the purposes of the research described in this form.  - You understand that your participation in this study will be anonymous. This means that it will not be possible to make a link between you and the information you provide.  - We will protect the information by restricting the access to the dataset to the members of the research team only. Data will be stored on Qualtrics’ servers, password-protected computers, and password-protected cloud services. Note that privacy cannot be guaranteed for data files uploaded to cloud services located on U.S. or European servers as they are subject to the USA Patriot Act, General Data Protection Regulation, and other local privacy laws.  - We intend to publish the results of the research. However, it will not be possible to identify you in the published results.  - We will securely store your anonymous information after the end of the study for possible replication of the findings or secondary use of your anonymous data in the future.    F. CONDITIONS OF PARTICIPATION  - You do not have to participate in this research. It is purely your decision and you can stop at any time. Should you wish to withdraw your participation during the study, simply stop answering the questionnaire and your incomplete data will be removed from the dataset. Should you wish to withdraw your participation by the end of the study, you will be able to indicate as such in the last question of the questionnaire. Note that you cannot withdraw your participation once you have completed and closed the study because your recorded data will be anonymous; we will thus be unable to remove your recorded data from the dataset.  - You will not be offered any compensatory indemnity for participating in this research.  - There are no negative consequences for not participating, stopping in the middle, or asking us not to use your information.    G. PARTICIPANT’S DECLARATION  I have read and understood this form. I have had the chance to ask questions and any questions have been answered. I agree to participate in this research under the conditions described.
MrAB1: Person A was given two tickets to the lottery. They won $150 with one ticket and $50 with the other ticket.      Person B was given a ticket to one lottery. They won $200.        Who is happier?
Game1_1_1: You are going to a sold-out game of your favorite local sports team and you have an extra ticket. The price marked on the ticket is $15 but this ticket has been offered to you by a friend for free.       You want to get rid of the extra ticket and you know the ticket’s face value price is $15. You find someone who wants the ticket. There is no law against charging more than the price marked on the ticket.    What price do you ask for selling the extra ticket if the person you sell it to... ? - Is a friend
Game1_1_2: You are going to a sold-out game of your favorite local sports team and you have an extra ticket. The price marked on the ticket is $15 but this ticket has been offered to you by a friend for free.       You want to get rid of the extra ticket and you know the ticket’s face value price is $15. You find someone who wants the ticket. There is no law against charging more than the price marked on the ticket.    What price do you ask for selling the extra ticket if the person you sell it to... ? - Is a stranger

Drink1: You are on the beach on a hot day, and you would really like a cold drink. A friend offers to go buy the drink from a fancy resort hotel. They ask how much you are willing to pay for the drink: they will only buy it if it costs as much or less than the price you state. You trust your friend, and there is no possibility of bargaining with the bartender.    What price do you tell them?

Debriefing: The survey you have completed aims to replicate the mental accounting effect. According to this phenomenon a person attributes different values to the same amount of money based on subjective criteria. Specifically, people tend to subjectively organize economic resources into different mental accounts. In addition, in this study, we measured some individual differences that might have an influence on mental accounting. In particular:   	  	   ●	Scale to measure financial literacy (Lusardi and Mitchell, 2014).  	 	 	  ●	Demographic data (e.g. gender, age or income level)	    Finally, we inform you that we have also used an attentional check to measure respondent engagement. The purpose of this study could not be fully revealed at the beginning of the study to avoid influencing your answers. Now that you have received this information, we ask you to confirm your consent to participate in this study or to withdraw it. In the latter case your data will not be used and will be deleted.
